data.text:

Wikimedia subject-area collaboration

WikiProject Automobiles exists to co-ordinate the effort to compile articles on all types and classes of automobiles, automotive parts and technology of the automotive industry. Additionally, it has the goal of presenting all articles in a consistent, legible and informative format. WikiProject Automobiles is a child project of WikiProject Transport, and a parent project of WikiProject Japan/Japanese car taskforce. See the talk page for proposals and discussion related to this WikiProject.

Instead of using the standard {{stub}} template, you may want to use one of the following more specific automobile stub tags, some of which are:

{{auto-stub}} or {{vehicle-stub}} for stubs about general automotive topics. Unfortunately, those categories contains many articles, so use of one of the more targeted subcategories is recommended:

{{motorvehicle-company-stub}} - for stub articles about automotive companies

{{auto-factory-stub}} - for stub articles about automotive factories

{{automotive-part-stub}} - for stub articles about automotive parts or components

{{automotive-tech-stub}} - for stub articles about automotive technologies

{{veteran-auto-stub}} - for stub articles about veteran automobiles produced before 1905

{{brass-auto-stub}} - for stub articles about brass-era automobiles produced from 1905-1915

{{vintage-auto-stub}} - for stub articles about classic automobiles produced from 1915-1930

{{classicprw-auto-stub}} - for stub articles about pre-war automobiles produced from 1930-1945

{{classicpow-auto-stub}} - for stub articles about post-war automobiles produced from 1945-1975

{{modern-auto-stub}} - for stub articles about modern automobiles produced after 1975

{{truck-stub}} - for stub articles about trucks (from our sister WikiProject Trucks)
